18/05/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgaria and Russia are discussing final details of an agreement on nuclear fuel waste processing in Russia.
In line with a preliminary agreement, Russia will import for processing 20 metric tonnes of used nuclear fuel from the Kozloduy nuclear power plant.
Bulgaria will pay $130,000 for the transport costs.
The fuel waste will likely be delivered in June.
In other news, Bulgaria's Finance Ministry introduced a package of measures Friday (16 May) aimed at preventing the trafficking of goods.
The planned steps include closing duty-free shops alongside highways and ports, introducing new excise duty stamps featuring a hologram sticker and establishing a tax police force.
Other duty free shops would remain open.
(Standart - 17/05/03;
BTA, BGNES, Ekho Moskvy- 16/05/03)
